content.text: {"summary_md":"Status: partial progress toward Conjecture 7.2 (units in the Habiro ring Z[q]^N are exactly ±q^i). Proven/established: torsion units are trivial (u^m=1 ⇒ u=±1); p-adic congruence along μ_{p^∞}: for odd p and primitive p^a-th roots ζ one has u(ζ) ≡ u(1) (mod p); a corrected rigidity lemma: if a unit u satisfies u(ζ)=±ζ^i for infinitely many roots of prime-power order ζ then u=±q^i (uses injectivity of τ over that infinite set). Key caveats: the claim for Laurent-polynomial units is not automatic from inclusion Z[q,q^{-1}]⊂Z[q]^N; the proposed 'chain injectivity' extension contains a gap. Next steps: settle non-unit of γ_m, prove Laurent-polynomial unit characterization, pursue prime-power rigidity to produce infinitely many exact equalities. Citations: proofs.md (formalized proofs), papers/paper1.tex (Habiro 2002).","highlights":["Torsion units in Z[q]^N are trivial: u^m=1 ⇒ u=±1 (rigorous).","p-adic congruence: for odd p and primitive p^a-th roots ζ, u(ζ)≡u(1) (mod p) in Z[ζ].","Rigidity (corrected): if unit u attains ±ζ^i at infinitely many prime-power-order ζ then u=±q^i (uses τ injectivity over that infinite set).","Inclusion-of-rings caveat: u∈Z[q,q^{-1}] being a unit in Z[q]^N does not follow automatically from ring inclusion—needs extra arguments (norms/values).","The proposed 'chain injectivity' (divisibility chains with p-power steps) has a critical gap and should not be used as is.","Concrete next technical targets identified: show γ_m(q)=∑_{i=0}^{m-1}(-1)^i q^i is non-unit for odd m≥3; prove Laurent-polynomial unit characterization; develop prime-power rigidity arguments."],"next_questions":["Prove γ_m(q)=∑_{i=0}^{m-1}(-1)^i q^i (odd m≥3) is not a unit by finding a prime p│m with γ_m noninvertible in Z[q]/(Φ_p,p).","Prove (or disprove) the Laurent-polynomial claim: if g∈Z[q,q^{-1}] maps to units in Z[ζ] for infinitely many ζ then g=±q^i (use Kronecker-type norms/height).","Clarify target formulation of Conjecture 7.2 (unit-group statement vs. general τ-injectivity for arbitrary infinite Z) and prioritize which route to complete next."]}
